('galileo-ai',
 'Galileo AI',
 'AI UI design tool that generates full interface screens from text descriptions',
 'Galileo AI is a generative AI tool for UI designers that converts text prompts into complete, editable interface mockups. A prompt like "a fitness tracking dashboard with weekly progress charts and a workout log" produces a full screen design with components, spacing, and colour that follows modern design conventions. The output is not a rough wireframe - it uses real UI components with proper layout grid, type hierarchy, and visual polish. Designs export directly to Figma, where they can be handed off to developers or refined further. Galileo AI is particularly useful at the beginning of a project when exploring directions quickly: a designer can generate ten different layout approaches in the time it would take to sketch one. The tool understands design system conventions, so the output is rarely arbitrary - it applies patterns familiar from established apps and platforms. This speeds up the exploration phase significantly without replacing the refinement and thinking that makes final designs excellent.',
 NULL,
 'https://usegalileo.ai',
 'https://usegalileo.ai',
