('diagram',
 'Diagram',
 'AI design tools for Figma - generate UI, rename layers, and write UX copy automatically',
 'Diagram is a collection of AI-powered Figma plugins that extend the design workflow with generative capabilities. The flagship plugin, Genius, generates UI components inside Figma from a text prompt - a button, a card, a form - directly in your existing design file. The Automator plugin batch-processes tedious tasks: renaming layers by content, applying consistent naming conventions to a messy Figma file, or converting text layers to auto-layout. The UX Writer plugin generates placeholder copy for designs - headlines, button labels, error messages - in the brand voice and tone of the product. Together, these plugins reduce the low-value repetitive work in design: layer cleanup, copy placeholder writing, and initial component drafts. Diagram sits inside the Figma workflow rather than requiring a separate tool, which makes adoption nearly frictionless for existing Figma users.',
 NULL,
